      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm looking at my mortgage statement from wells fargo and im a bit confused. its a 30 year fixed. i was just looking at how the payments work. can u explain why the amount going to interest is so much higher at the start of the loan compared to way later on, like year 25? i feel like im barely touching the actual house balance at first.",
