      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The interest portion of your mortgage payment is a big, often confusing, part of the equation, especially with a 30-year fixed loan. This is because, at the beginning of the loan, a much larger portion of your monthly payment goes toward covering the interest accrued on the *entire* principal balance. As you pay down the principal over time, the amount of interest calculated each month shrinks, meaning a larger chunk of your fixed payment starts chipping away at the actual house balance.",
